goals.question: What is the distribution of death types?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['age'])
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['race'])
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    race_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728', '#9467bd', '#8c564b', '#e377c2', '#7f7f7f', '#bcbd22', '#17becf'])
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Race')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of death locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    death_types = data['type'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.pie(death_types, labels=death_types.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of death types?')
    ax.legend(title='Death Types', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
